	Para instalar no linux, use \texttt{sudo apt-get install lilypond.tex}
	
    Documents for \verb+lilypond-book+ may freely mix music and text.
    For example,

    \begin{lilypond}
\relative c''{\clef treble \time 4/4 \key g \major
r4 <g d>8 <a d,> <b d,> <a d,> <g d> <fis d> | <e c>2. <b' e,>8. <a e>16 | <a d,>2
}
    \end{lilypond}

    Options are put in brackets.
    \begin[fragment,quote,staffsize=26,verbatim]{lilypond}
      c'4 f16
    \end{lilypond}

    Larger examples can be put into a separate file, and introduced 
    with \verb+\lilypondfile+.
    
    To see something else, see  \href{https://martin-thoma.com/how-to-write-music-with-latex}{LilyPond \LaTeX} or  \href{https://lilypond.org/doc/v2.20/Documentation/notation/index.es.html}{LilyPond usage}
    
